1
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:36,920
Yunkui,

2
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:38,890
I have one more favor to ask.

3
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:39,800
Tell me.

4
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:41,810
Do you know about

5
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,330
the development of the New Fourth Army

6
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:45,840
in the Nuoxi area?

7
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,280
Well,

8
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:52,340
I'm just focusing on organizing the militia in Haiwen.

9
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,000
I don't really pay attention to

10
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,440
the affairs of the New Fourth Army,

11
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:57,039
nor do I know much about them.

12
00:01:57,759 --> 00:02:00,620
Xie Yufeng from the Anti-Japanese Advance Column.

13
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:01,820
Do you know him?

14
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,250
His defense area

15
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,280
is nearby,

16
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,280
but we don't interact much.

17
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:10,979
I just came back from Ge Zhiyuan's place.

18
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:13,220
Your interaction with Xie Yufeng...

19
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,080
I know.

20
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,160
It's just regular contact.

21
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,820
Isn't everyone talking about

22
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,960
the Anti-Japanese National United Front now?

23
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,920
Many of us

24
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:23,360
are deceived by the Communist Party's disguise.

25
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,920
Brother Zhang, you know the past of the two parties.

26
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:26,980
Don't be deceived.

27
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,890
The Japanese are not that scary right now.

28
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:35,520
With the current lukewarm engagement between the two armies,

29
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,560
we have a vast territory and a large population.

30
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,000
We can hold them off.

31
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,240
When the Allied Forces free up their hands,

32
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:43,440
the situation will definitely change.

33
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,400
But the power of the Communist Party

34
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,800
is growing too fast and too fiercely.

35
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:51,480
It has greatly exceeded Officer Gu's expectations in the War Area,

36
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:54,010
and it deeply worries Generalissimo Chiang.

37
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:57,440
The Communist Party is organizing civilians everywhere.

38
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,960
They are like a flood of savage beasts.

39
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:00,760
If they don't restrain themselves,

40
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,420
the Communist Party will become a major threat.

41
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:05,040
Officer Gu and Chairman Han

42
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,460
are about to make a move against them.

43
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:12,360
Of course, that's impossible right now.

44
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:15,120
I want to use your place

45
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,920
to invite Xie Yufeng, Ge Zhiyuan,

46
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,760
and those militias.

47
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,840
Let's celebrate the Mid-Autumn Festival together

48
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,900
and discuss the anti-Japanese plan.

49
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:27,160
What do you think?

50
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,240
I just said it.

51
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,760
I don't have much contact with him.

52
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:32,480
He is a guy

53
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,240
who is very elusive.

54
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:38,000
I'll give it a try, okay?

55
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,280
Okay.

56
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,040
Xiaoyue,

57
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:45,640
go to Nuoxi immediately

58
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,800
and bring Xie an important message.

59
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,720
Tell him

60
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,400
it's a trap, don't come.

61
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,640
Does it have to do with the special envoy?

62
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,440
Yes. Make sure you tell Xie in person.

63
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:55,400
Is the province going to create friction with the Communist Party?

64
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,480
It's not a small friction this time.

65
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:58,600
They want to drive the New Fourth Army out of Nuoxi completely.

66
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,680
I just have one thing to say:

67
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,560
do not come.

68
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,730
Okay, I understand.

69
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,760
Wait a minute.

70
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,220
Be careful on the road.

71
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,160
Okay.

72
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,240
Shopkeeper,

73
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,130
I want a can of fish and a can of chicken.

74
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,960
Sure, please wait a moment.

75
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,080
These just arrived in the last couple of days, they are very fresh.

76
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:34,720
Okay.

77
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:37,020
Do you need anything else?

78
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:38,920
Yujiao.

79
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,520
You...

80
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:42,210
Sister-in-law.

81
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:43,300
Yujiao!

82
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,290
Sister-in-law!

83
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,520
Liao, Yujiao.

84
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,320
Liao!

85
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,360
No,

86
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,840
didn't you...

87
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,880
board

88
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,159
the Meiyun with Uncle?

89
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:51,880
Yeah.

90
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,610
We didn't board the Meiyun.

91
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,800
We took a ship to Shanghai.

92
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:59,700
That's wonderful!

93
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,770
Why are you in Shanghai too?

94
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,600
It's a long story.

95
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,480
After we parted ways last time,

96
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,410
I went to Xuzhou.

97
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:08,600
By the end of the Battle of Xuzhou,

98
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,330
our troops were all scattered.

99
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,650
Sun Huaiyi died,

100
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,380
and my leg was injured.

101
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,560
The situation was very chaotic then,

102
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,000
so there was no time for treatment.

103
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,840
At its worst,

104
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,600
I couldn't even walk.

105
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,250
A friend told me that

106
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,960
hospitals in Shanghai could perform surgery,

107
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,890
so Madam and I diverted to Hong Kong

108
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,690
and secretly came to Shanghai.

109
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:27,840
And now?

110
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,120
Is the injury better?

111
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:30,280
I can walk fine now.

112
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,320
But on rainy days,

113
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,210
my bones ache badly.

114
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:35,880
Chongqing felt

115
00:05:36,159 --> 00:05:38,240
it would be difficult for me to return to the battlefield,

116
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,970
so they assigned me other work.

117
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:43,000
So we're temporarily staying in Shanghai.

118
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,440
That's great.

119
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:46,920
Enough about us.

120
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,040
How are you?

121
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,040
Yeah, how are you?

122
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,920
A lot has happened since we arrived in Shanghai.

123
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,240
Sister-in-law, come with me.

124
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:57,720
Okay.

125
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:58,820
Liao, you come too.

126
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,600
This is

127
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,680
Yunkui's son.

128
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,650
He was born in Shanghai.

129
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:09,880
His name is Yueming.

130
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:11,440
His grandfather named him.

131
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:14,000
That's wonderful. Our godson.

132
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,520
I'll wake him up.

133
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,200
No,

134
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,200
let him sleep.

135
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:18,960
He's so beautiful.

136
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,090
Looks just like you.

137
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,840
How is Uncle doing now?

138
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,000
My father and Wanfu,

139
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,240
back in Nanjing,

140
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:32,060
the orderly who delivered the sword for Yunkui.

141
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:32,480
They are currently

142
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,520
locked up in the No. 76 prison.

143
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,930
For no clear reason,

144
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,159
they've been detained for a long time.

145
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:39,280
How could this happen?

146
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:40,080
Yeah.

147
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,200
Why don't you sit for a while?

148
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,280
I'll go to the restaurant across the street to get some food,

149
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,080
and we can eat and talk.

150
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:47,800
Okay.

151
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,680
Wait for me.

152
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:59,320
This kid looks so healthy.

153
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:02,120
Liao,

154
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,320
should we tell Yujiao

155
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:07,100
that Yunkui went to Wuhan?

156
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,620
What should I tell her?

157
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,520
I mean, how do I say it?

158
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,080
Should I tell her

159
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,600
that the Ministry of War used the carrot and stick

160
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,040
to make Yunkui take all the blame

161
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,480
for Sun Huaiyi?

162
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,400
Or should I tell her

163
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:24,400
that Deputy Minister Huang ordered all of us who know

164
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,080
to keep the truth a secret forever?

165
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,760
Then at least let The Zhangs know

166
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,840
that Yunkui might still be alive.

167
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:31,920
Are you sure Yunkui is really alive?

168
00:07:41,159 --> 00:07:41,960
Word has it

169
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,260
that Yunkui was ambushed by the Japanese

170
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,800
at the field hospital.

171
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:51,420
But we can't completely trust this news.

172
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,540
Yunkui's fate is currently unknown.

173
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,659
How about this.

174
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,560
Wait until I have exact news,

175
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,560
and I'll tell Yujiao personally.

176
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,690
That's all we can do.

177
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:14,240
It's time to eat.

178
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,240
Officer Pan, come

179
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:17,300
and try my big bowl of noodles.

180
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:19,560
This

181
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,490
is a bit like the Huizhou rice bowl.

182
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,650
Are you planning to use this

183
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,320
to entertain our honored guest?

184
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,560
Isn't this a special time?

185
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,040
We need to overcome the difficulties together,

186
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,600
so make do with some noodles.

187
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,480
Besides, we still have mooncakes here, don't we?

188
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,640
Didn't I tell you

189
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,340
to prepare a Mid-Autumn Festival dinner

190
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,140
and invite Xie Yufeng and Ge Zhiyuan over

191
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,679
for a chat?

192
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,299
Where are they?

193
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,880
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

194
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,560
Everyone is having fun with their families.

195
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,120
No one will come even if I invite them.

196
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:48,840
Come.

197
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,580
Let me tell you.

198
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,560
Regarding the handling of Xie Yufeng,

199
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:53,240
you must consider it

200
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,320
from the perspective of the Party-State.

201
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,200
This is related to

202
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,840
your reinstatement, your promotion in rank,

203
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,280
and the restoration of your reputation.

204
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,240
If he comes,

205
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,020
we can have a good talk with him

206
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,280
about how to reorganize his troops.

207
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,340
If he doesn't come,

208
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,760
he is destroying

209
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,520
the KMT-CPC United Front.

210
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:12,140
I will, in the name of the Theater Commander,

211
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,280
issue an ultimatum

212
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:16,480
for them to leave the Nuoxi area immediately.

213
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,080
Who said I wasn't coming?

214
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,560
Here I am.

215
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,920
Yunkui, do you have noodles?

216
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:26,720
Yes.

217
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,560
Isn't it all ready?

218
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,290
Right, let me introduce you first.

219
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,320
Officer Pan,

220
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:33,740
Commander Xie.

221
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,520
Jishan, long time no see.

222
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,560
Xie, it's been a while.

223
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,760
Good. Please have a seat.

224
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:44,440
Go ahead.

225
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,320
Didn't I tell you not to come?

226
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,660
Since I'm here,

227
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,600
let's spend the Mid-Autumn Festival together.

228
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,720
Thanks for your trouble, Yunkui.

229
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,250
Let me get you some noodles.

230
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,200
Okay, that's enough.

231
00:09:56,200 --> 00:10:00,040
Brother Yufeng, since you are here,

232
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:03,320
I'll get straight to the point.

233
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,690
Do you have any plans

234
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,520
to join the KMT?

235
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,000
We communists

236
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:14,450
have always been responding to

237
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:16,240
Generalissimo Chiang's call

238
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,700
to resist the Japanese and save the country.

239
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:21,320
Then have you heard Generalissimo Chiang say,

240
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:23,360
one ideology, one political party,

241
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,280
one leader?

242
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,020
Jishan, you invited me here today

243
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:30,520
to discuss plans against the Japanese.

244
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,170
So I would like to ask you

245
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,860
if there are any specific topics to discuss.

246
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,160
Someone reported you,

247
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:40,640
saying you seized territory, established a government,

248
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:43,620
collected taxes on your own, and plundered troops.

249
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,760
Are these true?

250
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:45,640
No.

251
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,330
Every piece of our defense zone

252
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:51,000
was seized from the Japanese and puppet troops.

253
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,240
And we fully respect

254
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,000
the Nationalist Government behind enemy lines.

255
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,240
We only organized

256
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,880
a mass organization

257
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,440
called the Anti-Enemy Association,

258
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,770
calling for rent and interest reduction.

259
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,570
Establishing a government

260
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,280
is purely fictitious.

261
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,240
And plundering troops

262
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,560
is also groundless.

263
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,920
Recently, regarding Brigade Commander Ge's 3rd Security Brigade,

264
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:16,120
there were indeed dozens of guerrillas

265
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,000
who came to us.

266
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,720
But this is their own freedom.

267
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,960
Of course, we also took the initiative

268
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,800
to contact Brigade Commander Ge regarding this matter,

269
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,530
hoping to properly resolve it.

270
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,360
You said someone reported us.

271
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,520
You can call that person here

272
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,720
so we can confront them face to face.

273
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,480
Xikou Town

274
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,160
was originally Brigade Commander Ge's jurisdiction.

275
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:39,880
Since you took it back from the Japanese,

276
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,480
you should return it to him.

277
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:42,960
Sincere cooperation

278
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,180
should be based on good faith, right?

279
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:48,160
Jishan, do you know?

280
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,720
This Xikou Town

281
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,800
was precisely abandoned by Brigade Commander Ge on his own initiative.

282
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,320
In the battle to recapture Xikou,

283
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,080
the Japanese lost more than 30 people,

284
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,320
while we sacrificed

285
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,640
over 80 heroic sons and daughters.

286
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,320
And more than half of them

287
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,760
were local civilians.

288
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,320
The problem right now

289
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:08,450
is not whether we want to return it.

290
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,700
It's that even if we want to return it,

291
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,640
the civilians wouldn't agree.

292
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,560
Well, about this matter.

293
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:18,040
Unite in the resistance and eliminate misunderstandings.

294
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:20,760
I think it's best to incorporate your Nuokang troops

295
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,960
into the National Revolutionary Army.

296
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,840
The New Fourth Army is originally the National Revolutionary Army,

297
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:28,640
the Newly Organized Fourth Army.

298
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,480
And the Nuokang Advance Column

299
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:33,570
is also under the jurisdiction of the Third War Zone.

300
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,440
Brother Xie, you might not know this,

301
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:37,170
but the Nuokang Advance Column

302
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,160
has been explicitly banned.

303
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:42,320
All future operations will be illegal.

304
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,690
Then I would like to ask,

305
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,220
was it banned by the Japanese,

306
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:49,720
or by the Wang puppet government?

307
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:52,650
It was requested by Commander Gu of the Third War Area

308
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:55,720
and approved to be banned by the Military Affairs Commission.

309
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,680
Do the Military Affairs Commission and Commander Gu

310
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:02,280
want to ban our anti-Japanese resistance in the occupied areas?

311
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,200
Brother Jishan.

312
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,140
You invited me here today,

313
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:14,520
saying we were to discuss grand strategies against the Japanese.

314
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,520
To tell the truth,

315
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:18,170
many of my comrades advised me not to come,

316
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:19,600
but I came anyway.

317
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,680
Because I trust you.

318
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,160
In July of the 26th Year of the Republic of China,

319
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,490
I followed Vice Chairman Zhou to Mount Lu for negotiations.

320
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,420
You were one of the comrades who received us.

321
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,200
Vice Chairman Zhou gave a speech

322
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:35,660
on KMT-CPC cooperation to face the national crisis together.

323
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:38,480
At that time, you were standing right across from me.

324
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,040
I saw you crying then.

325
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:41,480
I cried too.

326
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,560
I cried because

327
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,240
from then on,

328
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:47,160
Chinese people could finally

329
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,220
stop fighting other Chinese people.

330
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:53,440
Brother Jishan, today I would like to ask you.

331
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,040
Why were you crying

332
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,720
back then?

333
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,980
To reclaim your defense zone.

334
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,720
We still need to persist in the war of resistance.

335
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,920
Persisting in the resistance means opposing surrender,

336
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,360
right?

337
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:15,120
Jishan, I'd like to share two phrases with you.

338
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:18,960
Uphold unity, oppose division.

339
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:23,720
Uphold progress, oppose regression.

340
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,640
For over three years,

341
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:28,000
the Kuomintang and the Communist Party have stood together.

342
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,720
We've shared the same boat and fought bloody battles

343
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,800
to achieve today's results.

344
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:36,400
Essentially, anti-communism

345
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:40,120
is preparing to surrender to the Japanese.

346
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:41,600
Right?

347
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,520
I think this is not only us,

348
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:47,240
but also the 400 million

349
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:50,240
compatriots who refuse to be slaves of a ruined nation

350
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,160
would not want to see.

351
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:57,560
Xie.

352
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:00,440
No, Commander Xie.

353
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:02,560
I understand your words.

354
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:07,400
Commander Zhang, what's your opinion?

355
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:09,240
What I mean

356
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,200
is that

357
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,650
Commander Xie is right.

358
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:16,160
Chinese shouldn't fight Chinese.

359
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:19,360
What we hate are the warlords who hoard troops,

360
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:20,680
abandon cities and territories,

361
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,440
and oppress the people.

362
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:25,250
We hate traitors like Wang Jingwei even more,

363
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:27,280
who are anti-communist, divide the country,

364
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,440
and sell out the country for personal gain.

365
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,800
Not those Communists who actively resist Japan

366
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,800
and insist on KMT-CPC cooperation.

367
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,650
We are brothers in arms.

368
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,520
We must share a common hatred for the enemy and persist in resisting Japan.

369
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:41,000
Our guns should be aimed at the Japanese,

370
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,720
at the Japs.

371
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:46,560
Commander Zhang, haven't I told you?

372
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,660
Think from the perspective of The Party-State.

373
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:50,640
Keep in step.

374
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,480
Officer Pan,

375
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,170
I can tell you very clearly.

376
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,000
Since the Battle of Shanghai in 1937,

377
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,760
I have never thought about returning to my original post.

378
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:57,800
All I hope is

379
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,980
that we can unite to resist Japan.

380
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,200
So that Chinese people,

381
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:03,640
the happiness and peace we have been looking forward to,

382
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:04,840
and family reunions,

383
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:06,920
can come sooner.

384
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:13,520
Well said, Yunkui.

385
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:15,760
Reunion,

386
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,160
I think, is the simplest wish

387
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:21,280
in the heart of every Chinese.

388
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,560
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

389
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:24,120
It's rare

390
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:27,680
that we all have a break from the war.

391
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,360
To sit down and chat.

392
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:32,120
We miss our families more during festivals.

393
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:35,200
Come, today the three of us Chinese

394
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,400
will share a mooncake together.

395
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,180
Because in the future,

396
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,440
the battles may be very fierce.

397
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:46,120
I hope we can unite as one

398
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,520
and drive out the Japanese invaders as soon as possible.

399
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,560
What do you say?

400
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:00,040
Yunkui.

401
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:26,280
Does anyone want a mooncake?

402
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,240
I want some.

403
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:29,840
Everyone gets one.

404
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,240
One piece for each.

405
00:17:35,040 --> 00:17:35,360
Here you go.

406
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,220
I want some too.

407
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,120
I want some too.

408
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:37,780
Here you go.

409
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:38,840
Don't fall.

410
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:39,920
Thank you.

411
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,360
Kids,

412
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,040
happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

413
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,960
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

414
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:49,280
Here, Yujiao.

415
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:50,080
Your package.

416
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:50,720
Mine.

417
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:52,280
Miss Li.

418
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,040
Is it delicious?

419
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,240
Please continue handing these out.

420
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:54,960
Okay.

421
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:56,200
What is this?

422
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:58,240
This was sent to my place before,

423
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,400
saying it should be passed on to you.

424
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,660
Since I left Shanghai,

425
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,800
it took a while to finally receive it.

426
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:05,800
These are donations from the public for the children.

427
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:35,800
Miss.

428
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,680
What's wrong, Yujiao?

429
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:49,560
It's from Mr. Tian.

430
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,320
Then our Yueming, when you grow up,

431
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:10,680
you must also be

432
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,720
a great hero like Dad,

433
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:13,600
okay?

434
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:17,600
Yueming's dad is a great hero.

435
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,640
Wanfu is a great hero.

436
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,320
Wanfu

437
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:28,600
is cooking in the kitchen.

438
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:31,560
The 24th Year of the Republic of China.

439
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,840
I drove it in the Alps.

440
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:36,880
Now it can only serve as an ornament.

441
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,240
I can't break out of this room.

442
00:19:40,120 --> 00:19:41,840
He grew up with me.

443
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,320
Shouldn't I

444
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:44,900
have left him all alone

445
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,720
in that police station,

446
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:48,760
in that cold morgue?

447
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,320
I should have brought him home, right?

448
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,800
A sane Don Quixote

449
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,600
is of little use.

450
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,120
A crazy one

451
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,000
is endlessly fascinating.

452
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,200
I would rather hope

453
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:04,250
that Don Quixote stays crazy for the rest of his life.

454
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,760
I just don't want my factory

455
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,400
to produce things

456
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:12,280
that will help the Japanese invade us.

457
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,480
I especially don't want,

458
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,560
and I absolutely cannot let my machinery factory

459
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:18,560
be converted into a Japanese arsenal to make bullets.

460
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,920
Bullets made

461
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,600
to slaughter us Chinese.

462
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:23,240
No, absolutely not.

463
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:25,200
Not even one.

464
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:27,160
My match factory,

465
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:30,160
as soon as I put it up for sale, many people scrambled for it,

466
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:32,040
and it sold for a very good price.

467
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:34,280
You don't need to worry about me.

468
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:49,720
This is what Mr. Tian left for you.

469
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:56,200
Since Mr. Tian sent the check to you,

470
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:59,040
his intention is very clear.

471
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:02,600
Then on behalf of Mr. Tian,

472
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,520
I will donate it to the New Fourth Army.

473
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:08,240
I think Mr. Tian will certainly be happy

474
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,600
and gratified.

475
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,000
Thank you.

476
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,010
Your mooncakes are quite good.

477
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:32,120
Open the door.

478
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:34,800
Go inside.

479
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,300
Close the door.

480
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:38,760
Thanks, Hei.

481
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,120
Go eat your mooncakes.

482
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:40,800
Let's go.

483
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:50,680
Master! Master!

484
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:53,440
Here, have some water.

485
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:55,520
I don't want to drink.

486
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:56,920
Just have a sip.

487
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,040
It's sugar water.

488
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:09,520
And look here.

489
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:17,280
Look what this is.

490
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,160
Mooncake.

491
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,840
Aren't you afraid they'll beat you?

492
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:24,760
Don't worry.

493
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,240
They forced me to make mooncakes for them.

494
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,600
This is what's left.

495
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,640
Mooncake.

496
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,680
I wonder if Yujiao

497
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:44,000
and Yueming

498
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,760
will have mooncakes to eat.

499
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:51,840
Wanfu.

500
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,080
No, no.

501
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,880
Master, I already ate.

502
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,600
Would a cook ever go hungry?

503
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,800
These are all for you.

504
00:22:58,480 --> 00:22:59,160
Okay.

505
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:05,880
Okay.

506
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:09,960
Master.

507
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:13,160
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

508
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:14,440
To you too.

509
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:25,440
Sis, does everyone in the New Fourth Army know how to weave straw sandals?

510
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:26,200
Of course.

511
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:28,120
Every one of us knows how.

512
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:30,600
You have to keep your waist tight to weave them tightly.

513
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:31,200
Got it.

514
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:37,880
Sis, you said before that you were a primary school teacher.

515
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:39,560
Then why did you

516
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,280
join the New Fourth Army later?

517
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,400
Here, you try.

518
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:45,280
Like this?

519
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:55,320
When the Battle of Shanghai broke out,

520
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:57,640
my hometown

521
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,200
fell too.

522
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,040
Schools were closed.

523
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,520
Teachers lost their jobs, and students couldn't go to school.

524
00:24:03,520 --> 00:24:05,180
Everyone scattered and fled.

525
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,680
That time

526
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,890
was also my most confusing period.

527
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,840
Many young people who couldn't attend school

528
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:15,840
fled to the town in my hometown

529
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:17,820
from Shanghai and Ningbo.

530
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:20,680
A group of young people uncertain about the future

531
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:23,720
gathered to chat and discuss.

532
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:25,720
For hot-blooded youths,

533
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,160
staying in the occupied areas

534
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,090
would surely madden them to death.

535
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:32,080
If we continued to flee inland,

536
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:35,760
the journey would definitely be difficult and humiliating.

537
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:38,760
The more we talked, the more grieved and indignant we became,

538
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:41,520
and we couldn't wait to join the front line

539
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:42,320
to fight.

540
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,740
I also signed up for a youth corps.

541
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:45,960
At that time, I thought

542
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:48,560
signing up meant I could go to the front line to fight the Japanese.

543
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:51,680
Who knew this corps not only didn't resist Japan,

544
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:54,040
but its warlord-like style

545
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,440
was also very serious.

546
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:57,360
I couldn't stay for another moment.

547
00:24:57,360 --> 00:24:58,880
I discussed it with everyone,

548
00:24:58,880 --> 00:24:59,940
we quit this corps,

549
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,520
and we went straight to Wuhan.

550
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:03,180
Some went to the army academy,

551
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,160
and some enlisted directly.

552
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:07,360
Some went to the National University.

553
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:09,640
My two best friends and I

554
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:13,200
had always longed for the Anti-Japanese Military and Political University in Yan'an,

555
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:15,000
so we went straight to Hankou,

556
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:17,720
to the office of the 18th Group Army.

557
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,880
The 18th Group Army?

558
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,980
That's the Eighth Route Army.

559
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,300
Unexpectedly,

560
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:26,680
the leader of the Eighth Route Army Office actually met with us

561
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:28,340
and listened to our thoughts.

562
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:30,040
That leader was very kind.

563
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,560
He told us

564
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:34,400
that the road to Yan'an was tough,

565
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:35,940
food was scarce there,

566
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:37,640
and he was worried we wouldn't eat well.

567
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:38,440
So he asked us

568
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:40,640
if we wanted to join the New Fourth Army,

569
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:43,170
as this troop was also fighting the Japanese.

570
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,720
Actually, my original name was Fu Youying.

571
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:49,320
'You' as in young, and 'Ying' as in hero.

572
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,200
Because I'm the youngest in my family.

573
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:55,040
But I really disliked the character 'You'.

574
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:57,640
So when I was signing up for the New Fourth Army,

575
00:25:57,760 --> 00:25:58,840
I was thinking,

576
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:02,640
I came here on a sailboat

577
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,360
to fight against the Japanese.

578
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,960
So I wrote

579
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:07,160
'Fu Fan' on the form.

580
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:08,680
Later I found out

581
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,610
that most people had changed their names.

582
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,480
It was somewhat like

583
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:16,040
a kind of ritual.

584
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,330
What kind of ritual?

585
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:24,440
Like saying goodbye to our old names

586
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,400
and our past selves.

587
00:26:27,640 --> 00:26:28,570
Saying goodbye.

588
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:29,680
At that moment,

589
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:32,600
I really felt like I saw a new life

590
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,360
and a new me.

591
00:26:35,080 --> 00:26:36,000
I

592
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:39,040
chose a new me.

593
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:40,960
It was as if

594
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,920
I was truly reborn.

595
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:47,900
This feeling can only be sensed, not explained.

596
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:51,720
Sis,

597
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:54,810
I also want to cut my hair short.

598
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,080
It would look much neater.

599
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:11,520
For the greater good of the Anti-Japanese National United Front,

600
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:13,240
our superiors finally ordered us

601
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,170
to withdraw from Nuoxi in batches.

602
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:15,970
Don't worry.

603
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,520
Those dozen or so wounded soldiers left behind,

604
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:19,800
we will hide them well and take good care of them.

605
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:20,520
Thanks.

606
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,400
Yufeng,

607
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:29,450
I still feel sorry for you guys.

608
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:32,180
Don't be sorry.

609
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:34,320
Seeking unity through struggle

610
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,640
ensures unity survives.

611
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:38,840
Seeking unity through concession means unity perishes.

612
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:41,120
Besides, we have already struggled.

613
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:43,880
We've united with you, Magistrate Fan,

614
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:45,620
and have a broad mass base.

615
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:46,740
That is enough.

616
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:48,400
Actually, come to think of it,

617
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,930
I'm a bit worried about you.

618
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:52,360
What will you do after you go back?

619
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,120
Don't worry.

620
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:54,240
With Magistrate Fan around,

621
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:56,040
Ge Zhiyuan or Jishan

622
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:58,340
won't be able to do anything to me.

623
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,700
As for the KMT army,

624
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:02,090
I definitely won't go back.

625
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:03,680
But when it comes to resisting the Japanese,

626
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:04,720
I will stick to it

627
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:06,140
until the very end.

628
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:08,360
Yunkui,

629
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,540
just like what we said at the steel plant,

630
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:14,520
let's not talk about dying, let's talk about living.

631
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:15,580
Live tenaciously.

632
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,450
No matter when or where,

633
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:18,880
survive tenaciously,

634
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:19,880
and also

635
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:22,620
create favorable conditions for yourself.

636
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:26,320
Actually, I've been wondering.

637
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,240
What exactly did I lose?

638
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,130
I used to be obsessed

639
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:31,240
with removing the hat of a runaway general,

640
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:32,920
vindicating myself

641
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:34,600
and vindicating my 6,000 brothers.

642
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:38,320
But when

643
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:40,080
such an opportunity actually comes,

644
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:42,210
I thought about dying for the country,

645
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:43,880
succeeding or dying in the attempt.

646
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:45,280
This is a soldier's glory

647
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:46,400
and bounden duty.

648
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,960
I asked my orderly

649
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:50,280
to take my sword as a token

650
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,880
and send it back to my father in Nanjing.

651
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,320
For me, sending it back

652
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,600
means I have fulfilled my loyalty and duty.

653
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:59,480
But ironically, I didn't die.

654
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,400
I've been fighting all the way

655
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,600
until today.

656
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,560
I asked myself,

657
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,620
'What have you achieved?'

658
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:11,640
'What kind of situation have you created?'

659
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:12,920
I told myself,

660
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:15,920
'No matter how many Zhang Yunkui die,

661
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,200
or even how many brothers of the 87th Brigade die,

662
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:20,040
have we really succeeded?

663
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,480
Have we really died for a just cause?'

664
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,520
So looking back,

665
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,280
that sword

666
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:32,370
doesn't mean much to me now.

667
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,060
To fight against the Japanese invaders,

668
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:37,560
why rely on that short sword?

669
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,640
Chiang Kai-shek issued the Zhongzheng Sword.

670
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:41,480
Yan Xishan

671
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:43,560
issued the Justice Sword.

672
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:45,600
He Jian issued the Wisdom Sword.

673
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,490
With so many swords issued,

674
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:49,410
are we fighting for the country

675
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:51,280
or for ourselves?

676
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:53,290
If we don't figure this out,

677
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:57,040
whose success

678
00:29:58,120 --> 00:30:00,120
and whose cause are we fighting for?

679
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:01,940
The sword in hand is tangible.

680
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:03,540
Frankly speaking,

681
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:05,080
it's just a piece of iron.

682
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:10,180
But the sword in the heart is intangible.

683
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:11,720
That

684
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,640
is the key to victory.

685
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,640
An intangible sword.

686
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:18,480
Yufeng,

687
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:21,140
by the Yangtze River in Wuhan,

688
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:24,680
we once talked about how the army and the people are the foundation of victory.

689
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:26,960
The intangible sword you just mentioned,

690
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,160
does it refer to this?

691
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:30,130
The 400 million people of China

692
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:33,140
are our final Great Wall of Steel.

693
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,360
Anyone can say this,

694
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:36,600
and say it beautifully.

695
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:40,060
But true integration of the army and the people,

696
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:43,240
is extremely difficult to achieve.

697
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:45,240
I

698
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:48,000
sincerely want to invite you

699
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,100
to Yancheng, Jiangsu,

700
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,720
our newly opened base,

701
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:53,640
to see for yourself.

702
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:55,400
Perhaps there,

703
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:58,700
you can find the answer in your heart.

704
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:02,280
I will think about it carefully.

705
00:31:09,960 --> 00:31:10,800
Take care.

706
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:11,680
Take care.

707
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,520
Move out.

708
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,000
Mr. Zhang, I'm leaving.

709
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:52,400
I'm following Fu Fan and the others to Central Jiangsu

710
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,930
to join the New Fourth Army.

711
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:57,180
Fu Fan told me to say goodbye to you in person,

712
00:31:57,640 --> 00:32:00,370
but I thought it would be better to write a letter.

713
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:01,240
All this time,

714
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,600
It seems that only when others need me

715
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,000
do I realize my own value.

716
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:08,240
But last night, Fu Fan told me

717
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,300
why she joined the New Fourth Army

718
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:12,000
and why she changed her name.

719
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,400
I felt like I was suddenly enlightened.

720
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,460
I suddenly knew in my heart

721
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:18,370
what kind of person I want to be.

722
00:32:19,840 --> 00:32:21,440
Since the Battle of Shanghai started,

723
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:23,570
the Japanese bombed my bridal chamber

724
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:25,760
and then bombed the Yu family in Wuhan.

725
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:29,120
Later, when I worked as a nurse at the Wuhan Military Field Hospital,

726
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,780
I saw the bloody battlefield for the first time.

727
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:33,960
I finally understood that

728
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:37,240
if the country cannot be protected, how can the home survive?

729
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,720
I feel that today,

730
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,620
anyone made of flesh and blood

731
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:42,360
can no longer tolerate this.

732
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:43,840
I often think,

733
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:45,480
although adding just me

734
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:47,280
won't make much of a difference,

735
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,160
but one more person

736
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:49,820
means a little more strength.

737
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,970
Only then will our China have hope.

738
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,120
Mr. Zhang,

739
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,520
I really think so.

740
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,530
I can't stand those cowards who won't resist.

741
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:02,080
From Fu Fan,

742
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:03,280
I saw

743
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:05,140
what I yearn to become in my heart,

744
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:06,920
and I saw

745
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,560
the world I long for.

746
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,460
I want to go to Central Jiangsu

747
00:33:11,080 --> 00:33:12,740
to see those female soldiers,

748
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,320
changing their names, cutting their hair short,

749
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:17,120
going to the battlefield, and engaging in civilian resistance.

750
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:17,600
To see

751
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:20,060
what kind of lives they are actually living.

752
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,280
I want to join the New Fourth Army

753
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,740
and become one of them.

754
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:27,240
Mr. Zhang,

755
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:29,570
we are about to part.

756
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:31,440
I remember

757
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:34,180
the first time I saw you in the ruins of Wuhan.

758
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,120
I remember in the field hospital,

759
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:37,360
when I fed you herbs.

760
00:33:38,640 --> 00:33:41,200
I remember how you teased me with the thermometer.

761
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:44,480
I remember us folding grass boats by the Yangtze River.

762
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:47,010
I remember us making a charcoal car together.

763
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:48,520
I remember us together,

764
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:51,120
waiting for that seedling you planted to grow.

765
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:58,520
I can't really go on.

766
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:01,000
It's not like we'll never see each other again.

767
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,530
I hope the next time we meet,

768
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:04,760
you will see a brand-new me.

769
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:06,840
You also know

770
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:08,170
I don't know many words.

771
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:09,360
There are many typos,

772
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:11,219
and Fu Fan helped me correct them.

773
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:15,400
If you have time, please write me back.

774
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:17,679
So I can also know

775
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:19,880
about your recent life and mood.

776
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:21,679
Han Xiaoyue.

777
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:42,449
Liao has been arrested.

778
00:34:42,679 --> 00:34:43,719
Arrested?

779
00:34:44,679 --> 00:34:47,560
Tieshu, District Chief of the Shanghai District of the BIS, defected.

780
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:49,820
He has been arrested for five or six days.

781
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:54,929
Is the situation critical now?

782
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:58,560
As soon as Liao was arrested,

783
00:34:58,560 --> 00:34:59,960
he swallowed gold Douzi,

784
00:35:00,520 --> 00:35:04,050
and even swallowed an iron nail right in front of Lin Changgeng.

785
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:07,440
These intelligence agents forced him to eat leeks,

786
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,760
laxatives, and taro.

787
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,530
Finally, they gave him an enema

788
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:13,240
and saved him.

789
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:16,040
He's now locked in the VIP room of No. 76.

790
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:20,570
They asked me to go there

791
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:22,520
to persuade Liao to eat.

792
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:25,800
Liao has really suffered too much.

793
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:29,040
But he didn't defect.

794
00:35:29,720 --> 00:35:31,720
Instead, he put his life on the line,

795
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:33,520
forcing Lin Changgeng to go to Nanjing

796
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:35,780
to ask for instructions from Zhou Fohai.

797
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:37,920
I'm not sure exactly what was said,

798
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:39,040
but I know

799
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:41,560
Zhou Fohai promised him two things.

800
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:42,400
First,

801
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:44,560
they don't have to force Liao to defect.

802
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:45,240
Second,

803
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,040
on the premise of keeping him alive,

804
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:51,400
they are allowed to act according to circumstances.

805
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:53,460
They are treating Liao differently,

806
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:55,320
probably because they want something from him.

807
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:57,480
Yes, compared to defecting,

808
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:00,680
they obviously think he is more useful.

809
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,690
He's living in the VIP room now,

810
00:36:02,880 --> 00:36:05,920
much better than the first two days after his arrest,

811
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:07,760
with good food and drinks every day.

812
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:09,240
When those intelligence agents saw me,

813
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:10,700
they were all very polite.

814
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,560
He can even stroll in the yard when he's free.

815
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:15,000
Liao told me

816
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:18,210
that he has thought about many scenarios these days.

817
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:20,200
I guess they want to use Liao

818
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,600
to negotiate with Chongqing.

819
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:22,560
Negotiate?

820
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:25,480
That would make Chongqing the second...

821
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,120
Exactly.

822
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:28,680
Sister-in-law, we can't agree to this.

823
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:30,000
Of course not.

824
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:33,600
Negotiation means treason.

825
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:36,560
Liao and I both know it.

826
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:39,380
Let's not talk about this.

827
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:41,800
Liao asked me to tell you

828
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:44,440
that since No. 76 is treating him well

829
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:46,240
and Nanjing values him highly,

830
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:48,320
he will try to stall them

831
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:51,890
and save Uncle and the others as soon as possible.

832
00:36:58,640 --> 00:36:59,520
Mr. Liao,

833
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:01,200
your visit to our humble home today

834
00:37:01,200 --> 00:37:02,600
is a great honor.

835
00:37:03,280 --> 00:37:04,240
You have no idea.

836
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:06,840
Recently, our Changgeng has been

837
00:37:07,080 --> 00:37:08,400
running around for your business.

838
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:10,080
He really put in a lot of effort.

839
00:37:10,080 --> 00:37:12,140
Director Lin has indeed worked hard.

840
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:13,240
Not at all.

841
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,380
Brother Fengnian.

842
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:16,480
Brother Fengnian.

843
00:37:16,480 --> 00:37:17,640
Sorry.

844
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:18,480
Director Lin,

845
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:19,960
sorry to keep you waiting.

846
